						<summary>

						<p>This is a short inscription in early Pallava characters mentioning the <hi rend="italic">Vidyā-Parivādini</hi> which was a kind of musical instrument. It seems to state that this was developed by one Guṇasēna and was recommended for a particular kind of music.</p>						

